To create a class property for the variable `private static Vector3 _moveTo`, you can use the following syntax in C#:

```csharp
public static Vector3 MoveTo
{
    get { return _moveTo; }
    set { _moveTo = value; }
}
```

This creates a public static property named `MoveTo` that encapsulates the private static variable `_moveTo`. With this property, you can get and set the value of `_moveTo` from outside the class. Here's an example usage:

```csharp
// Set the value of the property
ClassName.MoveTo = new Vector3(1, 2, 3);

// Get the value of the property
Vector3 destination = ClassName.MoveTo;
```

Note that `ClassName` should be replaced with the actual name of the class in which you add this property.
